Customer emailed asking if the suspension "Air bladder" is covered. I replied it was not. This is the email that followed:Mr. Halko,
 
Good Morning.
 
This is getting frustrating for me as it seems that all the major items that need to get repaired are not covered under my extensive “Platinum” coverage warranty that I paid huge money for when I bought the truck.
 
Two months ago I had a major repair at Dodge with relation to the air springs and surrounding parts breaking due to the cold weather we had and apparently I got word from the guy I bought the truck from as he spoke to a claims rep and was informed that the tear or puncture was from the cold snap and Canada General wouldn’t cover it as they compared that to paint chipping off….not covered.  Total cost of the repair was over 2K.  The repair was due to cold weather not at any fault of my own and therefore should have been covered.
 
I’m seeing a trend here and if this continues….I’m going back to the dealership where I bought the truck and changing warranty companies…..I don’t think it is fair that I pay over 5K for a warranty for the peace of mind and only to have them not cover major parts that break down due to weather related matters or normal wear and tear and not something I caused and leaves me (the customer) out of pocket for tons of money despite having already paid over 5K for this warranty.
 
Can you please provide me with your Claims Manager’s contact info there (Email and phone)?
 
I think it is time that I reach out and get an explanation.
 
Thanks.
 
Greg Rushton


I explained that we have no record of his dealer calling and that I spoke with Doyle Dodge and simply told them the air bag is not covered. Customer asked to escalate. I suggested he call John D. A.H.
